byline.contributor: Reporting was contributed by Declan Walsh, Rukmini Callimachi and Rick Gladstone from New York, Helene Cooper and Eric Schmitt from Washington, and Aurelien Breeden from Paris.

abstract: Pro-government Libyan militias say they have captured city of Surt, Islamic State's last remaining stronghold in country; claim, if true, represents blow to militant group's efforts to expand in North Africa.

headline.print_headline: U.S.-Backed Militias in Libya Claim to Take Surt, an Islamic State Stronghold
headline.main: U.S.-Backed Militias in Libya Claim to Retake ISIS Stronghold of Surt
